<subSubSection id="E1DE65590530FFC988CEFD2016D4F400" pageId="1" pageNumber="298" type="description">
<paragraph id="A97B36D20530FFC988CEFD201410F0E1" blockId="1.[151,1437,500,2003]" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">
<emphasis id="9BB0EAC00530FFC988CEFD20162FF0BC" bold="true" box="[199,345,644,670]" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">Description.</emphasis>
<typeStatus id="767F88700530FFC98968FD2016BFF0BC" box="[353,457,644,670]" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">Holotype</typeStatus>
male: Total length, 
<quantity id="6E3C9B370530FFC98AA6FD201461F0BD" box="[687,791,644,671]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.85" pageId="1" pageNumber="298" unit="mm" value="18.5">18.5 mm</quantity>
; pronotum length, 
<quantity id="6E3C9B370530FFC98BE6FD20133FF0BD" box="[1007,1097,644,671]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.4" pageId="1" pageNumber="298" unit="mm" value="3.4">3.4 mm</quantity>
; pronotum width at its widest point, 
<quantity id="6E3C9B370530FFC988D6FD0C164EF0E1" box="[223,312,680,707]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.8" pageId="1" pageNumber="298" unit="mm" value="5.8">5.8 mm</quantity>
; elytral length, 
<quantity id="6E3C9B370530FFC989EFFD0C153BF0E1" box="[486,589,680,707]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.45" pageId="1" pageNumber="298" unit="mm" value="14.5">14.5 mm</quantity>
; humeral width, 
<quantity id="6E3C9B370530FFC98B00FD0C1414F0E1" box="[777,866,680,707]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.6" pageId="1" pageNumber="298" unit="mm" value="6.6">6.6 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A97B36D20530FFC988CEFD6F1534F128" blockId="1.[151,1437,500,2003]" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">
<emphasis id="9BB0EAC00530FFC988CEFD6F163CF0C4" bold="true" box="[199,330,715,742]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">Coloration.</emphasis>
Pronotum and head orange to dark brown; elytra black with yellow orange pattern. Venter lime green to light blue; Setae light yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A97B36D20530FFC988CEFCB7156FF19C" blockId="1.[151,1437,500,2003]" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">
<emphasis id="9BB0EAC00530FFC988CEFCB7167AF10C" bold="true" box="[199,268,787,814]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">Head.</emphasis>
Coarsely and densely punctate with punctures joined or separated by about 1-3 puncture diameters, except at middle of clypeus, and antennal tubercles where it is mostly free of punctures. Frons with pubescence conspicuous composed of numerous fine, long, and tangled setae. Vertex without median longitudinal groove. Antennae serrated from antennomere 4. Clypeus very sparsely setose, with anterior margin distinctly concave. Last maxillary palpomere oval (
<figureCitation id="31FF2A570530FFC989CFFC00157DF19C" box="[454,523,932,958]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1878,1902]" captionTargetBox="[236,1349,236,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-27@2.[225,1362,181,1854]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Conognatha (Pithiscus) spp. 1–3, Holotype male of C. (P.) continua sp. nov. 1, Dorsal view. 2, Ventral view. 3, Lateral view. 4, Size comparison between C. (P.) continua (left), and C. (P.) caparaoensis (right). Scale bars = 5 mm. 5–9, Holotype male of C. (P.) continua sp. nov. 5, Holotype labels. 6–7, Aedeagus, ventral and dorsal view. 8, Elytral detail. 9, Head, frontal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6535018" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6535018/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A97B36D20530FFC988CEFC6C120BF609" blockId="1.[151,1437,500,2003]" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">
<emphasis id="9BB0EAC00530FFC988CEFC6C1635F1C0" bold="true" box="[199,323,968,994]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">Pronotum.</emphasis>
1.7 wider than long; much narrower than base of elytra; with sides narrowed from base, feebly arcuate at middle, then narrowed to anterior angle. Finer and less densely punctate than head, with punctures separated by about 1-3 puncture diameters. Pubescence not very conspicuous but composed of numerous fine and long setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A97B36D20530FFC988CEFB971255F66C" blockId="1.[151,1437,500,2003]" box="[199,1315,1075,1102]" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">
<emphasis id="9BB0EAC00530FFC988CEFB971635F66C" bold="true" box="[199,323,1075,1102]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">Scutellum.</emphasis>
Small; pentagonal, with anterior margin straight; 1.3 times wider than long; impunctate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A97B36D20530FFC988CEFBF315EBF720" blockId="1.[151,1437,500,2003]" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">
<emphasis id="9BB0EAC00530FFC988CEFBF31663F650" bold="true" box="[199,277,1111,1138]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">Elytra.</emphasis>
2.2 times as long as wide. Interstriae convex from base to apex; striae impunctate. Elytral pattern composed of a rounded spot on each side of the scutellum, and two sinuous transverse bands near middle (median) and before the apex (pre-apical); the median band extends along the lateral margin to below the humeral angle. Apical margin strongly dentate, with 14 teeth on each elytron, of which the two most apical are stouter and longer than the rest and separated by a distinct notch.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A97B36D20530FFC988CEFAA814B0F74C" blockId="1.[151,1437,500,2003]" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">
<emphasis id="9BB0EAC00530FFC988CEFAA81661F704" bold="true" box="[199,279,1292,1318]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">Venter.</emphasis>
Pubescence as on pronotum. Fine and densely punctate with punctures separated by more than four times a puncture width. Punctures along midline of prosternum thicker and more conspicuous than on rest of the surface. Prosternal process flat and without anterior prominence (
<figureCitation id="31FF2A570530FFC98B7AFAF014CFF74C" box="[883,953,1364,1390]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1878,1902]" captionTargetBox="[236,1349,236,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-27@2.[225,1362,181,1854]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Conognatha (Pithiscus) spp. 1–3, Holotype male of C. (P.) continua sp. nov. 1, Dorsal view. 2, Ventral view. 3, Lateral view. 4, Size comparison between C. (P.) continua (left), and C. (P.) caparaoensis (right). Scale bars = 5 mm. 5–9, Holotype male of C. (P.) continua sp. nov. 5, Holotype labels. 6–7, Aedeagus, ventral and dorsal view. 8, Elytral detail. 9, Head, frontal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6535018" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6535018/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A97B36D20530FFC988CEFAD317A4F7DD" blockId="1.[151,1437,500,2003]" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">
<emphasis id="9BB0EAC00530FFC988CEFAD31648F7B0" bold="true" box="[199,318,1399,1426]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">Aedeagus.</emphasis>
Parameres finger-like in apical third, apex rounded bearing around six long setae. Median lobe wide basally, gradually narrowing to the apex which is pointed and markedly exceeds the apex of the parameres. Visible part of ventral surface with vertical wrinkles at the base, centrally depressed surrounded by raised borders (
<figureCitation id="31FF2A570530FFC98D6DFA6417B3F7DD" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1878,1902]" captionTargetBox="[236,1349,236,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-27@2.[225,1362,181,1854]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Conognatha (Pithiscus) spp. 1–3, Holotype male of C. (P.) continua sp. nov. 1, Dorsal view. 2, Ventral view. 3, Lateral view. 4, Size comparison between C. (P.) continua (left), and C. (P.) caparaoensis (right). Scale bars = 5 mm. 5–9, Holotype male of C. (P.) continua sp. nov. 5, Holotype labels. 6–7, Aedeagus, ventral and dorsal view. 8, Elytral detail. 9, Head, frontal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6535018" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6535018/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">Figs. 6–7</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A97B36D20530FFC988CEF9A316D4F400" blockId="1.[151,1437,500,2003]" box="[199,418,1543,1570]" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">
<emphasis id="9BB0EAC00530FFC988CEF9A31653F400" bold="true" box="[199,293,1543,1570]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E1DE65590530FFC988CEF98814E5F490" pageId="1" pageNumber="298" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="A97B36D20530FFC988CEF98814E5F490" blockId="1.[151,1437,500,2003]" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">
<emphasis id="9BB0EAC00530FFC988CEF98816A7F464" bold="true" box="[199,465,1580,1606]" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">Differential diagnosis:</emphasis>
The new taxon is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="6EC44D510530FFC98B1DF9881271F464" authority="Portela &amp; Mermudes, 2014" authorityName="Portela &amp; Mermudes" authorityYear="2014" box="[788,1287,1580,1607]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="298" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coffeatus" subGenus="Pithiscus">
<emphasis id="9BB0EAC00530FFC98B1DF9881458F464" box="[788,814,1580,1606]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">C.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="9BB0EAC00530FFC98B36F9891422F464" box="[831,852,1581,1606]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">P.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="9BB0EAC00530FFC98B6DF98814BFF464" box="[868,969,1580,1606]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">coffeatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="CD554B230530FFC98BD8F9881271F464" author="Portela, C. &amp; Mermudes, J. R. M." box="[977,1287,1580,1606]" pageId="1" pageNumber="298" pagination="114 - 124" refId="ref2269" refString="Portela, C. &amp; Mermudes, J. R. M. (2014) Two new species of Conognatha Eschscholtz, 1829 (Coleoptera, Buprestidae, Stigmoderini) from Southeast and South Brazilian regions with distributional notes. Zootaxa, 3857 (1), 114 - 124. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3857.1.5" type="journal article" year="2014">Portela &amp; Mermudes, 2014</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="6EC44D510530FFC98D1AF98816BCF448" authority="Portela &amp; Mermudes, 2014" authorityName="Portela &amp; Mermudes" authorityYear="2014" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="298" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puris" subGenus="Pithiscus">
<emphasis id="9BB0EAC00530FFC98D1AF988125AF464" box="[1299,1324,1580,1606]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">C.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="9BB0EAC00530FFC98D34F9891224F464" box="[1341,1362,1581,1606]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">P.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="9BB0EAC00530FFC98D6AF98912EBF464" box="[1379,1437,1581,1606]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">puris</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="CD554B230530FFC9889EF9F416BCF448" author="Portela, C. &amp; Mermudes, J. R. M." box="[151,458,1616,1642]" pageId="1" pageNumber="298" pagination="114 - 124" refId="ref2269" refString="Portela, C. &amp; Mermudes, J. R. M. (2014) Two new species of Conognatha Eschscholtz, 1829 (Coleoptera, Buprestidae, Stigmoderini) from Southeast and South Brazilian regions with distributional notes. Zootaxa, 3857 (1), 114 - 124. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3857.1.5" type="journal article" year="2014">Portela &amp; Mermudes, 2014</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="6EC44D510530FFC98A0DF9F41499F448" authority="Pineda &amp; Barros, 2017" authorityName="Pineda &amp; Barros" authorityYear="2017" box="[516,1007,1616,1643]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="298" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caparaoensis" subGenus="Pithiscus">
<emphasis id="9BB0EAC00530FFC98A0DF9F41568F448" box="[516,542,1616,1642]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">C.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="9BB0EAC00530FFC98A27F9F51535F448" box="[558,579,1617,1642]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">P.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="9BB0EAC00530FFC98A5AF9F5159EF448" box="[595,744,1617,1642]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">caparaoensis</emphasis>
Pineda &amp; Barros, 2017
</taxonomicName>
by dark elytral coloration with yellow orange, reddish or reddish-brown pattern (warm colors); and by having all interstriae convex from base to apex. 
<taxonomicName id="6EC44D510530FFC98D8AF9D01651F490" authorityName="Pineda &amp; Koike &amp; Barros" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="298" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="continua" subGenus="Pithiscus">
<emphasis id="9BB0EAC00530FFC98D8AF9D012EAF4AC" box="[1411,1436,1652,1678]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">C.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="9BB0EAC00530FFC988A8F93D17C0F490" box="[161,182,1689,1714]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">P.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="9BB0EAC00530FFC988CCF93D1651F490" box="[197,295,1689,1714]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">continua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished by characters given in the table 1.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E1DE65590530FFC988CEF9181372F5F0" pageId="1" pageNumber="298" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="A97B36D20530FFC988CEF9181305F4D8" blockId="1.[151,1437,500,2003]" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">
<emphasis id="9BB0EAC00530FFC988CEF9181624F4F4" bold="true" box="[199,338,1724,1750]" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">Etymology:</emphasis>
From Latin “ 
<emphasis id="9BB0EAC00530FFC989E1F9191523F4F4" box="[488,597,1725,1750]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">continuus</emphasis>
” (uninterrupted), in reference to the two uninterrupted elytral bands, one of the differential characters to separate the new taxon from the other three similar species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A97B36D20530FFC988CEF8A01343F544" blockId="1.[151,1437,500,2003]" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">
<emphasis id="9BB0EAC00530FFC988CEF8A01670F53C" bold="true" box="[199,262,1796,1822]" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">Note.</emphasis>
The recently described species 
<taxonomicName id="6EC44D510530FFC98A7BF8A0145EF53C" authorityName="Portela &amp; Mermudes" authorityYear="2014" box="[626,808,1796,1823]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="298" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coffeatus" subGenus="Pithiscus">
<emphasis id="9BB0EAC00530FFC98A7BF8A015FDF53C" box="[626,651,1796,1822]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">C.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="9BB0EAC00530FFC98A94F8A115C4F53C" box="[669,690,1797,1822]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">P.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="9BB0EAC00530FFC98ACAF8A0145EF53C" box="[707,808,1796,1822]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">coffeatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="6EC44D510530FFC98B68F8A0149BF53C" authorityName="Portela &amp; Mermudes" authorityYear="2014" box="[865,1005,1796,1823]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="298" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puris" subGenus="Pithiscus">
<emphasis id="9BB0EAC00530FFC98B68F8A0140DF53C" box="[865,891,1796,1822]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">C.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="9BB0EAC00530FFC98B84F8A114D4F53C" box="[909,930,1797,1822]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">P.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="9BB0EAC00530FFC98BBAF8A1149BF53C" box="[947,1005,1797,1822]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">puris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are known only from their 
<typeStatus id="767F88700530FFC98D21F8A012EEF53C" box="[1320,1432,1796,1822]" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">holotypes</typeStatus>
, which unfortunately seem to be lost in the fire that destroyed the Museu Nacional, Universidade Federal do 
<collectingRegion id="6B00F8300530FFC98D5BF88C179EF544" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
(MNRJ) in 2018. If this is the case, a 
<typeStatus id="767F88700530FFC98A9DF8E9159BF545" box="[660,749,1869,1895]" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">neotype</typeStatus>
designation will be required.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A97B36D20530FFC988CEF8D41372F5F0" blockId="1.[151,1437,500,2003]" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">
<emphasis id="9BB0EAC00530FFC988CEF8D41575F5A8" bold="true" box="[199,515,1904,1930]" pageId="1" pageNumber="298">Other material examined:</emphasis>
